Description: A Puffer fish, one of three studies for Plate 109 of the artist's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte, pendant les campagnes du Général Bonaparte', 1802 Pen and black ink
Producer name: Drawn by: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Curator's comments: Engraved by Denon for his 'Voyage...' (there is no copy of the book the Department. The B.L. copy is at 458.h.12). Lit.: P. Rosenberg (ed.), exhib. cat., Paris, Musée du Louvre, 'Dominique-Vivant Denon: l'oeil de Napoléon', 1999, no. 100
Exhibition history: 1999/2000 Oct-Jan, Paris, Musée du Louvre, Denon 1747-1825 2008/9 Oct-Mar, Paris, Institut du Monde Arabe, Napoleon et l'Egypte 2009 May-Oct, Arras, Musée des Beaux-Arts, Napoleon et l'Egypte
Associated names: Associated with: Napoléon I, Emperor of the French (Napoleon)
Illustration to: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Associated titles: Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte
